---
import Docs from '@/layouts/Docs.astro'

import { CATEGORY_COLORS, CATEGORY_LABELS, RULES } from '@/data/rules'
---

<Docs
  title="Rules Overview"
  description="All five astro-doctor ESLint rules with categories and default severities."
  editPath="apps/docs/src/pages/docs/rules/index.astro"
>
  <h1>Rules</h1>

  <p>
    astro-doctor provides five ESLint rules for <code>.astro</code> files, covering performance,
    accessibility, security, and best practices. All rules are enabled in the
    <code>recommended</code> config at their default severities.
  </p>

  <h2>All rules</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Rule</th>
        <th>Category</th>
        <th>Default</th>
        <th>Fixable</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {RULES.map(rule => (
        <tr>
          <td>
            <a href={`/docs/rules/${rule.slug}`}>
              <code>{rule.id}</code>
            </a>
          </td>
          <td>
            <span class:list={['inline-flex items-center rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium', CATEGORY_COLORS[rule.category]]}>
              {CATEGORY_LABELS[rule.category]}
            </span>
          </td>
          <td>
            <span class:list={[
              'inline-flex items-center rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium',
              rule.severity === 'error' ?
                'bg-red-500/10 text-red-400 border border-red-500/20' :
                'bg-yellow-500/10 text-yellow-400 border border-yellow-500/20'
            ]}
            >
              {rule.severity}
            </span>
          </td>
          <td class="text-[hsl(var(--ink-muted))] text-sm">—</td>
        </tr>
      ))}
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Rule categories</h2>

  <h3>Performance</h3>
  <p>
    Rules that help you ship faster pages. Covers hydration strategies
    (<code>no-client-load-overuse</code>) and image optimisation (<code>use-astro-image</code>).
  </p>

  <h3>Accessibility</h3>
  <p>
    Rules that ensure your pages are usable by everyone, including screen-reader users.
    Currently: <code>no-missing-alt</code>.
  </p>

  <h3>Security</h3>
  <p>
    Rules that prevent common vulnerabilities. Currently: <code>no-set-html</code> which flags
    unescaped HTML injection.
  </p>

  <h3>Best Practices</h3>
  <p>
    Rules that encourage idiomatic Astro patterns. Currently: <code>prefer-class-list</code>
    for conditional class composition.
  </p>

  <h2>Customising rules</h2>

  <p>Override any rule severity in your <code>eslint.config.js</code>:</p>

  <pre><code>{`import astroDoctorPlugin from '@santi020k/eslint-plugin-astro-doctor'

export default [
  ...astroDoctorPlugin.configs.recommended.config,
  {
    rules: {
      // Upgrade to error
      'astro-doctor/no-client-load-overuse': 'error',
      // Disable a rule
      'astro-doctor/prefer-class-list': 'off',
    },
  },
]`}
  </code>
  </pre>

  <p>Or use a <a href="/docs/configuration"><code>doctor.config.*</code></a> file for CLI-only overrides.</p>
</Docs>
